1. Setting up ReactJS
    a. create-react-app
    b. cd
    c. npm start

2. Running notes
    a. always export and import default and files
    b. have own files for running everything

3. Importing Images
    a. create a public folder on your folder = <img src={requires('./../../public/logo512.png')}>
    b. importing on top = import image from './../../public/logo512.png' = <img src={Logo} />

4. Importing Bootstrap
    a. search for npm i bootstrap@5.0.1
    b. paste it in terminal and install
    c. go to node module and import the bootstrap on the file you want to use

5. Packages Installed
    a. you can go to package.json to see what are the packages you installed
    b. npm i = means you are about to install

6. Assets folder
    a. images = other graphic file
    b. fonts
    c. logos = svg, png

7. Views folder
    a. web pages = about, contact, etc..

8. Components 
    a. navbars
    b. main page
    c. sidebar
    d. footer

9. Helpers / Contstant / Functions
    a. currency.js
    b. alerts / pops up
    c. reusability purposes

10. If you don't want to run it on package 3000
    a. go to pacakage json
    b. go to scripts and start
    c. --port=3030
